Get ready to go back to school at Ohio College Preparatory School with our Drive-Thru Ice Cream Social & FREE School Supply Giveaway!

The first 250 children will receive free school supplies! Enjoy free ice cream, meet our staff, and enroll for the 20-21 year. During this event we will be following best practices in social distancing to keep participants safe. Prior and throughout the event, surfaces will be sanitized. Families are required to wear face masks.

Families interested in enrollment should come prepared with the following:

Childâ€™s Birth Certificate

Proof of Residence

Parent ID (for primary, custodial parent)

Immunization Records

For more information about these documents, please visit our Enrollment Resources page here

March 27, 2020

Dear Parents & Caretakers,

Thank you for your continued support and flexibility as we work through these unprecedented times as a community. To help prevent the spread of COVID-19, our school is closed to students and the public until Monday, April 6th. At this time, it remains unclear if we will be able to re-open on that date or if the closure will be extended. In either case, learning will continue, and we will provide an update next week.

As educators, we miss seeing our students every day and are concerned for their well-being during this confusing time. Most importantly, we care about their safety and therefore support the government orders and recommendations that haveâ€¦

post_text:
Hello Ohio College Preparatory School Families!

I hope that everyone is safe and well. Please see the following updates regarding our meal service program:

In accordance with government orders to shelter in place, meal pick-up will be consolidated to once per week.

Beginning the week of March 30th, all five days of food will be available for pick-up during limited serving hours on Tuesdays from 9:00 AM to 11:00 AM at Steam Academy of Warrensville as opposed to Ohio College Prep.

If you plan to participate, each Tuesday you will pick up five breakfast and five lunch meals per student; therefore, please bring carrying bags or boxes.

For more information visit our COVID-19 webpage at: https://ohiocollegeprep.org/covid-19/

Please also check our Facebook and Instagram pages for more information.

Thank you and continue to be safe,

Mrs. Green

Dear Ohio College Preparatory Families,

We hope that you all are well. Due to Governor Dewine's mandated, "Stay At Home" Order, our office hours have been changed. We are open today, March 23, 2020 from 10:00am until 1:00pm, however the office and the school will be closed until further notice. As a reminder, report cards have been mailed out. Please check our Website, Facebook page and Instagram page for updates and other pertinent information. Thank you and please have a safe Spring Break!

The work provided will allow scholars to remain on track with their learning and progress towards grade level mastery. All materials are also available for pick-up in the school office from 9:00am to 3:00pm each day. Please contact the school office at 216.453.4550 with any questions.
